---
permalink: /tags/
pagination:
  include: Tags
  permalink_suffix: "tags/{{ num }}.html"
  order: Asc
---

<section id="intro" class="s-intro target-section">
    <div class="s-intro__bg rellax" data-rellax-speed="-7"></div>

    <div class="row s-intro__content">
        <div class="column">
            <div class="s-intro__content-about">
                {% if paginator.indexes %}
                    <h1 style="margin-bottom: 32px;">Tags</h1>
                    <ul style="margin-left: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">
                    {% for ptag in paginator.indexes %}
                        <li>
                            <a href="/{{ ptag.index_permalink }}/">
                                <i class="fas fa-tags" aria-hidden="true"></i> {{ ptag.index_title }} ({{ ptag.total_pages }})
                            </a>
                        </li>
                    {% endfor %}
                    </ul>
                {% else %}
                    <h1 style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><i class="fas fa-tags" aria-hidden="true"></i> {{ paginator.index_title }}</h1>
                    <ul style="margin-left: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">
                    {% for page in paginator.pages %}
                        <li><a href="/{{ page.permalink }}">{{ page.title }}</a>
                    {% endfor %}
                    </ul>
                {% endif %}

                <div class="s-intro__content-social">
                    {% unless paginator.indexes %}
                    <a href="/tags/">
                        <i class="fas fa-tags" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    </a>
                    {% endunless  %}
                    <a href="/">
                        <i class="fas fa-home" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="about" class="s-about target-section">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="column large-3 tab-12">
            <img class="s-about__pic" src="images/avatar.jpg" alt="">
        </div>
        <div class="column large-9 tab-12 s-about__content">
            <h3>About Me</h3>
            <p>80s kid, music lover and software development passionist based in Dortmund, Germany. I'm not one of those highly talented early starters, already coding as a kid. Started my IT path in school. Achieved Bachelor in Information Technology. Dropped Master at around 80%. Life is not about a perfect CV, but passion for what you do. Software development. Software architecture. Art or engineering? Creativity or hard facts? So called soft skills or frameworks and technologies? Keep it balanced.</p>

            <p>Feel free to reach me through my profiles.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="resume" class="s-resume target-section" style="padding-bottom: 0px;">
    <div class="row s-resume__section">
        <div class="column large-3 tab-12">
            <h3 class="section-header-allcaps">Current Training Topics</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="column large-9 tab-12">
            <div class="resume-block">
                <p>
                    With more than 15 years of experience, anyone could create a page-long list of technical capabilities, frameworks, and libraries.
                    I don't think that would be useful.
                    So I'd like to give you some insights into topics that I'm currently trying to learn or improve.
                    Since this is largely done in my spare time, some of these topics may take some time.
                </p>

                <ul class="skill-bars-fat">
                    {% for skill in site.data.learning.skills %}
                    <li>
                        <div class="progress percent{{ skill.percentage }}"></div>
                        <strong>{{ skill.topic }}</strong>
                    </li>
                    {% endfor %}
                </ul>

                <p>To avoid any interpretation as to priority or focus, the topics are in alphabetical order.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
